Mix together flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder, and egg. The mixture will look like cornmeal. Peel, core, and slice the apples. Mix together with 1/2 tablespoon cinnamon. Place apples in a greased 8 inch square pan. Spread flour mixture over the apples. Mix together 1 tablespoon cinnamon and 1/4 cup sugar; sprinkle over the top of the crisp. Drizzle with butter or margarine. Bake at 300 degrees F (150 degrees C) for one hour. Serve warm.